Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.47,0:01:46.52,Default,,0,0,160,,{\blur1\b1\bord0\shad0\fade(400,400)\fs30\c&HE4D9D4&}Episode 5\N\N\N\N\N\N{\fs60}Clear After the Rain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.52,0:02:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous down there, Lucy-May!\NPlease come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May's {overarching }love for animals made her approach the flock of sea lions mindlessly and completely deaf to my importunities{ to stop}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.72,0:02:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:02:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright. Keep сalm{/ quiet} and I won't startle you.{/ do anything to you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.93,0:03:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you better not startle me either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.86,0:03:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Flee! Flee outta there, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.96,0:04:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! You alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.39,0:04:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone escaped{/ went} into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking standing idly, \Nsurrounded by sea lions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought how sea lions faces \Nare absolutely cute from near{/ close}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you really not one bit scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.41,0:04:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You spooked me. {You surprised me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so afraid they would eat \Nyou or something even worse.{I was sure they are gonna eat you on the spot any moment.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.08,0:04:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.67,0:04:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts to rain hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.16,0:04:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's find a shelter somewhere soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Under those rocks would do. Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.10,0:04:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out sea lions hate thundery rain{/ rain with lighting} as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.32,0:05:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy, we're already home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.82,0:05:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you are not wet at all! {/ you are almost dry.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.92,0:05:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sheltering from rain at Jamling's{ place}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I figured it won't stop shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.10,0:05:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Mr. Jamling{/ Ms. Jamling's husband} returned home at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.12,0:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard he went to{/ left for} Adelaide yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.59,0:05:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And he certainly was not planning to stay there{ overnight}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.41,0:05:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Jamling seems to grow really worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's also the {blowing }wind. \NThis rain is hardly stopping any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure hope your dad and Ben \Ndid not get sodden in Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.84,0:05:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind picked up, Mr. Jamling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We should get home sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.89,0:05:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we head out now, \Nwe'll get soaked to the skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.91,0:05:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife is probably pulling out her hair. {My household is getting crazy worried, I think.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:05:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not so far from here to the tents.\NBut not with that leg...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there is no fracture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's but a small sprain, \Nnothing to hinder me from walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.61,0:06:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When we get back to the tent, \Nwe should show you to a physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.49,0:06:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Physician? \NI thought there are no physicians around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no ashore, \Nbut one is stationed on the ship. {None reside here, but one does on the ship.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the naval surgeon. \NThe man that never gets sober. {The one that is constantly boozy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the only doctor we have. {That is the specifics of a quack's work.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Poppel, we should head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.61,0:06:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting soaked does not bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.53,0:06:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you furthermore, \Nbut would you mind to find a branch for me to use as a cane{/ walking stick}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to go home by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.18,0:06:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.34,0:06:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.17,0:06:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You did me an invaluable favor {truly saved my life}\Nby bringing me all the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.45,0:06:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to manage the rest{/ from here on} by myself somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.04,0:06:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I need a cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.61,0:06:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling, you will go there together with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:06:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll get wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.36,0:07:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Please mount my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.37,0:07:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Poppel...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This rain is not going to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.14,0:07:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.69,0:07:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Intuition tells me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.65,0:07:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it will be stopping shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.99,0:07:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.11,0:07:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Intuition tells me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be a copycat, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's how I really feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{No matter how long you wait /}Wait all you want,\Nthe sea lions are not coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.66,0:07:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting soaked here anyhow. \NLet's head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess. Mom might also start worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.61,0:07:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.48,0:07:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and I had our mighty share of worrying \Nwhen dad did not return from Adelaide last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.78,0:07:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,At a time like this, \Nthe sooner we return, the better. {/ I'd rather spare mom some worry.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, catch up quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, you remember the place \Nyou left your shoes, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.23,0:08:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.05,0:08:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't sound terribly confident to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.11,0:08:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am not confident. \NYou'll help us look for it, won't you, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.94,0:08:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Poppel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.89,0:08:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will your tent weather this intact?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.10,0:08:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If the wind grows any stronger than this, \Nsome of the tents are bound to get blown away.{/ , aren't they?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.44,0:08:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As for our tent, \Nit will certainly be safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, ours has nothing to fear as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.89,0:08:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our uncle has always been an inborn carpenter. {Our uncle is a connatural carpenter by trade.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, our dad, though a farmer by trade, \Nis a universal handyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, our tent is drum-tight. {/ stretched firmly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.13,0:08:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I also helped to stretch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. I sure hope when Billy grows up to your age, \Nhe makes just as helpful assistant to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.13,0:09:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Billy is ten, right? \NHe is the same age{/ was born the same year} as our Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.08,0:09:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, for instance, \Nis good for nothing in comparison to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You caught a cold already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a cold. \NJust some bug flew into my nose. {I just had something in my nose.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Clara is finally getting better, \NI'm about to get another older sister come down sick. {/ to nurse.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.55,0:09:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not getting sick, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.99,0:09:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.83,0:09:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think this rock looks familiar? {Lit: Is that rock not the right place?}\NThat's about where sis tossed her shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.54,0:09:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here{maybe comma will look good here as well but I want them to sound different} alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.72,0:09:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was certainly this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.81,0:09:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd, it should totally be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.88,0:09:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than standing there idly, \Nhelp me look for it, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.85,0:09:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatcha said?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.11,0:09:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I stepped on it{'something' would kinda kill CPS here}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.34,0:09:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.17,0:10:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know yet. \NBut it's so slippy{'slimy' may sound more disgusting here} to the touch...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.33,0:10:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you pull your leg out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.83,0:10:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.23,0:10:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It went to this side!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.72,0:10:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.66,0:10:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.54,0:10:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.37,0:10:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there even snakes like this? \NIt has proper legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.60,0:10:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's a lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, must be a lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It has like two heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.37,0:10:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It really does...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.38,0:10:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What a peculiar fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.33,0:10:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it will come out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.22,0:10:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to find out if it really does have two heads!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be a biting species...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.08,0:10:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it bite you, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.02,0:10:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,See? It did not bite even after being stepped on. \NIt's a good one. {It will be fine.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be averted \Nhad I heeded to mom's advice on safety{/ of wearing boots at all places}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.72,0:11:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.10,0:11:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Those parts are full of dangerous insects{/ bugs}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.21,0:11:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She told me to stay in boots at all times \Nso as to not get stung.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.48,0:11:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The head must be on the side it is walking forward with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This one right now was no insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.61,0:11:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Peculiar{/ Odd shaped} as it is, \NI still think is was a lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.30,0:11:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A lizard is even graver a case! \NI totally should have not taken off my boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.32,0:11:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Start looking for my boots!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way I'm setting an unshoed foot \Ninto that grass ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Boots?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Your boots are right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You found them in {\i1}that{\i0} place?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.96,0:11:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure to have tossed them yonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone must have brought 'em here, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! No other way around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.14,0:11:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But who would do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem like any of the immigrants reached here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would anyone fool around \Nwith some boots in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.44,0:11:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:11:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured it! \NI know who fooled around with boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.76,0:11:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.68,0:11:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look{ directly} at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sideways behind me, \Nsomeone is hiding behind the rock.
